text.tspan: Share of population with mental or substance disorders, male vs. female, 2017
Share of males vs. females with any mental health or substance use disorder; this includes depression, anxiety, bipolar, eating disorders,
schizophrenia, alcohol and drug use disorders, and neurodevelopmental disorders. Due to the widespread under-diagnosis, these estimates
use a combination of sources, including medical and national records, epidemiological data, survey data, and meta-regression models.
Data source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease
